2. Establish the relationship between S and the sum of three consecutive terms: Let T be the sum of the sums of all three consecutive terms, we get $3S=T+2a_1+2a_{16}+a_2+a_{15}$;
3. Enumerate the side length combinations of isosceles triangles with the smallest sum: Select the side length combinations of isosceles triangles with the smallest sum, exclude the combinations that cannot be consecutive, and determine the minimum sum of 14 triangles;
4. Minimum value verification: Minimize T and $2a_1+2a_{16}+a_2+a_{15}$, take $a_1=1$, $a_{16}=1$, $a_2=2$, $a_{15}=3$, calculate to get $3S≥149$, so S≥50;
5. Draw the conclusion: The minimum value of S is 50.
